This plugin contains content vendored from a claude.ai/design generated
bundle, fetched 2026-05-14 from

  https://api.anthropic.com/v1/design/h/MT9aywRAkLve4gaS6Vnkjw

The bundle name is "Deloitte x Databricks Alliance, Design System".

  - skills/crafting-presentations/references/deloitte-databricks-alliance/
      (entire subtree, vendored verbatim except for the punctuation
      substitutions described below)

The upstream bundle declares no license at time of port. Its README
states the logos are "stylized recreations" and substitutions for the
user to swap with official Deloitte and Databricks brand assets before
any external use. All rights to the original text remain with the
upstream author. The adaptations are mechanical and add no original
authorship. If the upstream license posture changes, this NOTICE should
be updated and files may need to be removed or relicensed accordingly.

Substitution rules applied at port time:

  (1) Sentence-pause "space U+2014 space" becomes ", " (comma + space).
  (2) Labelled-bullet "**name** U+2014 desc" becomes "**name**: desc"
      (the bold markers are preserved; the U+2014 plus its flanking
      whitespace becomes ": ").
  (3) Numeric-range "digit U+2013 digit" becomes "-" (hyphen).
  (4) HTML body copy may use the entity forms &mdash; / &#8212; /
      &ndash; / &#8211; in place of substitution where the visual
      em-dash matters. The per-skill em-dash lint matches raw
      codepoints, not entities.
  (5) Catch-all for code-comment em-dashes / en-dashes in .js and .css
      files (no surrounding-whitespace variant) substitutes the
      remaining codepoints to comma / hyphen respectively. This keeps
      the workbench-wide em-dash lint clean and matches the project
      convention that the lint scans the entire skill subtree.

